metadata.name: 5/1 ■ Den’ihacun the Dreamer
metadata.description:
Then, whoosh! Straight across the other side to Rho'lay. I can see that everything around me was rippled; it's like when you see your reflection in water. I had no idea that I could see so many color palettes as a human. That colossal granite tree looks like a dagger, waiting for its next victim.

"Welcome to my domain, Aki," he said, then he appeared behind me, which isn't a good sign! "You must have done a very good bargain with my brother, so tell me why you are here, and be quick; there are matters to be attended to." I said, "I want to go home, and I hope you can help me."

He weaved his hands in the air and created a vision, like you were looking through a glass. "Do you see that tower without any doors? There is a cosmic trident standing near the throne of my mother, Oth-Xa'rath. Bring that to me so that I can put an end to my nephew Ulx’o's exile. Then she can expand her domain and bring peace to our family. You know the way now!"

I felt a very powerful push, and I woke up!
